        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"281383\">@Richard Feldman</span></p>",
        "id": 260891023,
        "sender_full_name": "Locria Cyber",
        "timestamp": 1636510397
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Related to <a href=\"https://github.com/rtfeldman/roc/pull/1866\">https://github.com/rtfeldman/roc/pull/1866</a></p>",
        "id": 260891031,
        "sender_full_name": "Locria Cyber",
        "timestamp": 1636510412
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>sorry, what's the question?</p>",
        "id": 260911467,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1636511410
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>clap's API only borrows <code>str</code> with lifetime.</p>",
        "id": 260912579,
        "sender_full_name": "Locria Cyber",
        "timestamp": 1636511441
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I used a workaround by allocating Strings of backends in <code>main</code></p>",
        "id": 260913167,
        "sender_full_name": "Locria Cyber",
        "timestamp": 1636511458
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>can you link me to a specific line of code in the PR?</p>",
        "id": 260913824,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1636511674
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>inside <code>src/lib.rs build_app()</code></p>",
        "id": 260914236,
        "sender_full_name": "Locria Cyber",
        "timestamp": 1636511830
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><a href=\"https://docs.rs/clap/2.33.3/clap/struct.Arg.html#method.possible_value\">https://docs.rs/clap/2.33.3/clap/struct.Arg.html#method.possible_value</a></p>",
        "id": 260914253,
        "sender_full_name": "Locria Cyber",
        "timestamp": 1636511847
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>clap doesn't take ownership of <code>str</code> used</p>",
        "id": 260914265,
        "sender_full_name": "Locria Cyber",
        "timestamp": 1636511862
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>So you have to allocate that in  <code>main</code> to keep clap happy</p>",
        "id": 260914339,
        "sender_full_name": "Locria Cyber",
        "timestamp": 1636511890
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>lazy_static is elegant for \"compile-time variables\" since Rust has poor support for CTFE</p>",
        "id": 260915400,
        "sender_full_name": "Locria Cyber",
        "timestamp": 1636512450
    },
    {
        "content": "<div class=\"codehilite\"><pre><span></span><code>error[E0015]: calls in constants are limited to constant functions, tuple structs and tuple variants\n  --&gt; cli/src/main.rs:27:37\n   |\n27 |     const default_backend: String = Backend::default().to_string();\n   |                                     ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 260915404,
        "sender_full_name": "Locria Cyber",
        "timestamp": 1636512456
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>yeah, but it's more expensive than actually static things, or even inline things, because <a href=\"https://docs.rs/lazy_static/1.4.0/lazy_static/#implementation-details\">it has to do a lock on every dereference</a> to prevent data races</p>",
        "id": 260916054,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1636512777
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>that's probably an acceptable amount of overhead here, but it makes me want to avoid <code>lazy_static</code> by default</p>",
        "id": 260916500,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1636512822
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>regarding the earlier question - it looks like if we can't get a static lifetime for those, then we probably do need to do a heap allocation</p>",
        "id": 260916912,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1636512859
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"453395\">Locria Cyber</span> has marked this topic as resolved.</p>",
        "id": 260919933,
        "sender_full_name": "Notification Bot",
        "timestamp": 1636513006
    }
]